The paper discusses forward-error-correction (FEC) codes for high-speed optical communications, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The simulation results are based on field-programmable-gate-array (FPGA) implementation, which is related to computer systems and networking (cs.DS, cs.NI). The proposed error floor analysis technique is also relevant to system and information theory (cs.SI).
